","title":"No LLM code in dependencies","url":"https://joeyh.name/blog/entry/no_LLM_code_in_dependencies/","score":32,"flags":0,"comment_count":8,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"gioele","user_is_author":false,"tags":["practices","vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oe8pxn","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oe8pxn/no_llm_code_dependencies"},{"short_id":"3kvccm","created_at":"2026-07-02T11:33:28.000-05:00","title":".gitignore Isn’t the Only Way To Ignore Files in Git","url":"https://nelson.cloud/.gitignore-isnt-the-only-way-to-ignore-files-in-git/","score":41,"flags":0,"comment_count":2,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"abnercoimbre","user_is_author":false,"tags":["vcs"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/3kvccm","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/3kvccm/gitignore_isn_t_only_way_ignore_files_git"},{"short_id":"s99eqv","created_at":"2026-07-02T10:01:14.000-05:00","title":"WinPE as harness for Windows driver testing and fuzzing","url":"https://bednars.me/blog/winpe-harness","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"classichasclass","user_is_author":false,"tags":["windows"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/s99eqv","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/s99eqv/winpe_as_harness_for_windows_driver"},{"short_id":"ubl3i2","created_at":"2026-07-02T09:04:10.000-05:00","title":"Tools or techniques for conveying mental models?","url":"","score":19,"flags":0,"comment_count":12,"description":"\u003cp\u003eWhat are tools or techniques which well for conveying and growing mental model?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTechniques I have seen which work well include:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBuilding and maintaining the system (growing)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eScribbling on napkins or gesturing next to someone with a furrowed brow (conveying)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDocumentation which enumerates surface area or catalogs features may be exhaustive but often doesn't achieve either building or conveying the mental model of the subject in question. Using a well designed tool or product directly can achieve both.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat are the tools and techniques which work for you? What makes them effective?\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"What are tools or techniques which well for conveying and growing mental model?\r\n\r\nTechniques I have seen which work well include:\r\n- Building and maintaining the system (growing)\r\n- Scribbling on napkins or gesturing next to someone with a furrowed brow (conveying)\r\n\r\nDocumentation which enumerates surface area or catalogs features may be exhaustive but often doesn't achieve either building or conveying the mental model of the subject in question. Using a well designed tool or product directly can achieve both.\r\n\r\nWhat are the tools and techniques which work for you? What makes them effective?","submitter_user":"mw","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","philosophy","programming"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ubl3i2","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ubl3i2/tools_techniques_for_conveying_mental"}]